We see a lot of patients in our ED requesting MAT prescriptions that actually don't have any kind of emergency and could have been managed in the outpatient setting if there were adequate access to MAT clinics and PMDs who are comfortable with MAT.  We are happy to be part of the safety net for these patients, but it's kind of sad that our society has not created systems to treat these patients that function well enough or have enough access.  They should not have to come to the ED for routine Suboxone refills.

Buprenorphine is extremely effectivein treatment of cronic pain; yet there are several pratical problems:

[1] Organizational and administrative obstacles, most of which were listed in the questionnaire.
[2] Expense & insurance coverage
[3] Although the drug may be ideal for chronic pain in many cases, the patient may be stigmatized because of its frequent application in cases of opiate dependence.
Widely different coverage between public and private insurers and among private insurers.  My patients have been stigmatized by retail pharmacy staff when filling buprenorphine prescriptions.
